<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1270,1549]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Remarks: From a revision of material reported under this name from Sardinia (
<bibRefCitation author="Gerecke, R." box="[1117,1294,1307,1334]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="735 - 759" refId="ref74426" refString="Gerecke, R. (2014 b) The water mites of the genus Atractides Koch, 1837 (Acari, Hydrachnidia: Hygrobatidae) in Corsica and Sardinia. Zoosystema, 36 (4), 735 - 759. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2014 n 4 a 3" type="journal article" year="2014">Gerecke 2014b</bibRefCitation>
) results that the specimens in question represent in fact an undescribed species (described below as 
<taxonomicName authority="Gerecke, 2021" authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2021" box="[1142,1244,1343,1369]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castor" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1142,1244,1343,1369]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. castor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1253,1344,1343,1369]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). As the specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[338,424,1379,1405]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Corsica</collectingCountry>
and Sardinia were mostly reported from spring habitats, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2003" box="[1140,1261,1379,1405]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Atractides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="allgaier">
<emphasis box="[1140,1261,1379,1405]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">A. allgaier</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lives in middle order streams, this observation is consistent with its habitat preference. The collecting site in Lombardia has now in fact produced the first ascertained Italian record of the species.
</paragraph>
